# FRONTEND ARCHITECTURE RULES (FINAL)

## Tech Stack (Mandatory)

- React
- TypeScript
- MUI (Material UI)
- Redux Toolkit (UI state only)
- TanStack Query (server state)
- Axios (API layer)

---

# 1. STATE MANAGEMENT RULES

## 1.1 Server State (Backend Data)

- MUST use TanStack Query for all API data
- NEVER store API responses in Redux
- NEVER manually cache server data

Examples:
- user data
- lists, tables
- dashboard metrics
- API-driven forms

---

## 1.2 Client/UI State (Redux)

Use Redux ONLY for:
- authentication UI state
- modal open/close states
- theme mode (if needed beyond MUI)
- local UI filters (NOT backend-driven)

Rules:
- No async logic in slices
- No API calls in Redux
- Keep slices small and domain-based

---

## 1.3 Local State

Use React local state (`useState`, `useReducer`) for:
- form inputs
- UI toggles
- temporary component state

---

# 2. API LAYER RULES

- All API calls MUST be inside `/services`
- Services MUST be pure functions
- No React, no hooks inside services

Example:

```ts
export const getUser = () => axios.get("/user");
```

---

# 3. REACT QUERY RULES

- All API interactions MUST be wrapped in custom hooks
- Components must NEVER call services directly

Example hooks:
- useUserQuery()
- useCreateUserMutation()

Rules:
- Always use proper queryKey structure
- Enable caching by default
- Retry only for GET requests
- Mutations must handle loading/error states explicitly

---

# 4. HOOK LAYER RULES

Hooks are COMPOSITION layer only

Combine:
- API service
- React Query
- minimal UI logic

Rules:
- Hooks MUST NOT render UI
- Hooks MUST NOT contain business logic unrelated to data flow

---

# 5. REDUX RULES

- Use Redux Toolkit only
- No API calls in slices
- No side effects inside reducers
- Keep slices minimal and domain-focused

---

# 6. CONTEXT API RULES (STRICT)

Use Context ONLY for:
- auth session (lightweight global user info)
- theme or design mode
- feature flags
- dependency injection (services, config)

DO NOT use Context for:
- server state (use React Query)
- frequently changing UI state
- forms
- tables, filters, pagination
- large or complex data structures

### Prop Drilling Rule
- Prop drilling up to 2–3 levels is acceptable
- Do NOT replace simple prop flow with Context

### Performance Rule
- Context updates re-render all consumers
- Keep context small and stable
- Split contexts by domain:
  - AuthContext
  - FeatureFlagContext
  - ConfigContext

---

# 7. STYLING ARCHITECTURE

## 7.1 Theme is the single source of design tokens

Must include:
- colors
- typography
- spacing
- border radius
- shadows
- breakpoints
- component overrides

Rules:
- NEVER hardcode colors
- NEVER duplicate spacing logic

Use:
- theme.palette
- theme.spacing
- theme.typography

---

## 7.2 Styling Rules

- Prefer `sx` over `style`
- Avoid external CSS files
- Avoid inline styles unless strictly dynamic
- All reusable styling MUST come from theme or components

---

## 7.3 Component Wrappers (Lightweight Only)

DO NOT replace MUI completely.
Only create minimal reusable wrappers.

---

## 7.4 Base UI Components

```tsx
const BaseCard = ({ children, sx, ...props }) => {
  return (
    <Card
      {...props}
      sx={{
        padding: 2,
        borderRadius: 2,
        boxShadow: 1,
        backgroundColor: "background.paper",
        ...sx,
      }}
    >
      {children}
    </Card>
  );
};
```

Rules:
- Must stay generic
- No business logic
- No prop explosion

---

## 7.5 Extension Rule

✔ DO:
```tsx
const StatsCard = (props) => (
  <BaseCard sx={{ textAlign: "center" }} {...props} />
);
```

❌ DO NOT:
```tsx
<BaseCard variant="compact" shadow="none" rounded="xl" dense />
```

---

# 8. FOLDER STRUCTURE RULES

/features
  /auth
  /user
  /dashboard

/shared
  /components
    /ui
  /hooks
  /utils
  /constants

/services

---

# 9. CONSTANTS RULES

- No single global constants file
- Must be domain-based:
  - auth.constants.ts
  - user.constants.ts

---

# 10. MUI USAGE RULES

- Use MUI components as base
- Customize via theme first
- Wrap only when reuse is proven
- Prefer composition over replacement

---

# 11. CODE QUALITY RULES

- Components must focus on UI only
- Business logic must live in hooks/services
- No duplicate API logic
- No styling duplication outside theme/components
- Keep components small and composable

---

# 12. PERFORMANCE RULES

- Use React Query caching instead of manual caching
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Memoize only when needed
- Do not over-optimize prematurely
